         <abstract>
            <p>The marginal dependence structure of a dataset y is displayed by a scatterplot matrix, a matrix whose elements are scatterplots of each pair of variables. A natural way to view the conditional dependence structure of y is through a partial scatterplot matrix, which contains scatterplots of partial residuals. We discuss its construction and give two examples of its use.</p>
          </abstract>
